<br>
Then came the Kunark era when lure spells were first introduced, and non-Lure spells basically bounced off most raid targets' ultra high resists.  This was a low-point of mage DPS since our nukes were often resisted and our pets were &quot;risky&quot;.<br>
<br>
Then came the Velious era.  Wizards get unresistable Bane spells introduced. Resists were so high that our nukes bounced even worse off boss mobs.  Essentially, only Lures/Banes landed on alot of high end Velious content.  This was another hit to mage DPS, and since TRod was not yet in and pets ineffective and dangerous in ToV, mage raid DPS and usefulness hit its lowest point...aka the &quot;CoH whore era&quot;.<br>
<br>
Then came the Mid-Velious resist patch.  This lowered resists on Velious raid level mobs.  While still resisted often, mages were at least able to land nukes at times.  Wizard lures/banes are still used for most part. Mage DPS goes up somewhat, but pets still &quot;risky&quot;.  Mages at this point are a rarity in Norrath.<br>
<br>
Enter the Luclin era.  Again, no Lure spells added.  TRod added.  Moon mobs have lower resist rates so wizards push lures to back of book and use Draughts and big nukes for thier better ratios.  Wizard DPS hits all time high; mages' DPS is improved markedly as well, but so are all damage casters.  Pets still have &quot;risk&quot; issues on raids. Melee DPS drops on moon because of massive Luclin mob AC. Mages are doing well with good DPS and raid rods being needed.  Some retired mages come back.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Great Pet Patches of 2002&quot;  all pets get boosts and are made 'neutral' so across the board mages and other pet casters get a DPS increase since &quot;pet risk&quot; is gone.  This is the high point of mage DPS since pre Kunark. At this time damage casters are supreme.  Twink mages are rampant.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Luclin Retune&quot; - Mobs AC is lowered and resists are raised.  Melee DPS improves at the expense of caster DPS. Mages are not affected as much since their pets can now melee more effectively.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Great Resist Retuning&quot;. Very recently done, the resist system is changed.  Mobs that were formerly immune to some things are no longer, and vica versa.  This is a recent change and is still being explored, but mages specifically lose their pet elemental immunities.  Pet DPS on AoE mobs is lowered as a result, but haste cap came off as well, so remain about the same.  Mages are near balanced, except for a few remaining issues.<br>
<br>
This brings us to &quot;The Present&quot;....<br>
<br>
Planes of Power is less then two months away, and we get our first glimpse of the new spell lists.  Most upgrades for casters seem to be upgrades of Kunark era spells.  Mage nukes' ratios are not much improved.  Wizards get new bad-ratio lure spells for the first time since Kunark.<br>
<br>
If wizards are getting Lure spells again, this foreshadows PoP being the resist nightmare for mages that Kunark/early Velious was.  This would be disastrous for mages, since we have no lures as well as having access to only 2 of the 5 damage types (Fire and Magic).<br>
<br>
The poor upgrades for mages, as well as the presence of wizard lures tells us that mage nuking power in PoP will be severely lessened.<br>
<br>
Mages receive no &quot;raid-utility&quot; spells in PoP other then the limited usefulness of summoned mez/charm, so it looks like damage is the mages forte again....*but* our nukes are subpar and non-lure.  This leaves only one source for mage damage.  The new pets.<br>
<br>
These new pets will have to pick up the margin that mages will lose in nuking power for us to stay where we are in overall DPS.  Will VI give us pets able to do that?  We cannot know this, since pet spells cannot be parsed for damage, but since pets just got an upgrade, it is not likely pets in PoP will be that much better.<br>
<br>
All in all, this early information from PoP forebodes trouble for mages in this expansion, and with only 6 weeks to release I don't see alot of radical changes still to come.<br>
<br>
Welcome back to the World of Lure Only Mobs.  Kindly drop your rods over there in the corner.<br>
<br>
